<h2 id="section-top">Maternity services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1155">Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentec04bd86bfdb4f7f99ed2ce14f8fb054">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="pregnant woman" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=222410"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Your care before your baby is born (antenatal care) will be provided at Salford Royal.</p>
<p>You will have a choice of the following areas to have your baby:</p>
<ul>
<li>At home supported by midwives </li>
<li>The standalone Salford Birth Centre that opened in November 2011 which is <a href="http://www.cmft.nhs.uk/saint-marys">run by St Mary’s Hospital</a> </li>
<li>In a new or expanded and improved maternity unit nearest to where you live at either the  
<ul>
<li>Royal Bolton Hospital</li>
<li>Saint Mary’s Hospital in central Manchester, or </li>
<li>North Manchester General Hospital</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Care for you and your baby after the birth will be provided by midwives working in the community. Midwives visit women at home after the birth and see women in clinics and health centres in Salford.  Please see <a href="http://www.srft.nhs.uk/about-us/depts/feeding-baby/">Feeding your Baby</a> for more information.</p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
